Site Identifier: # Please be aware that some sample sizes may be very small. This is typical of species that are less commonly reported
Location: and particularly for open cup nesting birds. Any analyses conducted using sample sizes of less than 50 nest attempts for a single species during a single year should be interpreted very cautiously. Note: a nest attempt is any attempt where at least one egg or young were reported in the nest summary. Also note that these data are retrieved from nest summaries only and do not include any information from individual nest checks.
